<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text">This seral type replaces other long-persistent alliances following fire or perhaps other disturbance, such as intensive grazing or mechanical soil disturbance. For example, <i>Ericameria teretifolia </i>stands established in place of <i>Juniperus californica </i>stands burned 25 years ago in Anza-Borrego Desert State Park (Keeler-Wolf et al. 1998b). However, research on fire regime is lacking for this alliance.</div>
